THIEVERY "THIEVERY PERMIT" "STEALING PERMIT"

Usage:  diplomacy thievery <empire>

Thievery permits allow your empire to steal from the other empire. This permit
costs the same number of coins as a declaration of war (that is, the cost is
based on the disparity between the empires and is cheaper if the other empire
has offended you). This permit lasts 24 hours.

You don't need a thievery permit to steal if you're already at war.

The other empire will not be notified that you can steal from them. However,
they gain the ability to attack members of your empire until the permit
expires.

See also: DIPLOMACY, OFFENSE, STEAL
